3_16	0.073637687	That gave the new institution a government-wide reach.
3_17	0.088737158	In August 1814, an invading British army intervened.
3_18	0.094387505	It seized Washington and burned the White House and the Capitol.
3_19	0.29578581	The Library of Congress, which by then had about 3,000 volumes, was destroyed.
3_20	0.28180708	With one act, Jefferson became the founder of the Library of Congress as it now exists.
3_21	0.10953441	''I learn from the newspapers that the vandalism of our enemy has triumphed at Washington over science as well as the arts, by the destruction of the public library with the noble edifice in which it was deposited,'' Jefferson wrote in a letter that September.
3_22	0.089003726	By then retired to his home at Monticello, Jefferson offered Congress the opportunity to buy his private library which then totaled nearly 6,500 volumes.
3_23	0.07657936	The purchase was approved.
3_24	0.076044723	The price was almost $24,000.
3_25	0.20802464	Jefferson called it the ''choicest collection of books in the U.S''.
