9_24	0.098174889	In doing so, Hutson was performing excavation on a document that is a touchstone of American history.
9_25	0.088842953	The ``wall of separation'' metaphor, though not found in the Constitution, is often invoked as shorthand for the religion clause of the First Amendment to the Constitution, which says that ``Congress shall make no law respecting an establishment of religion, or prohibiting the free exercise thereof''.
9_26	0.088283905	The import of the ``separation'' language has been argued over by scholars and cited in at least 50 Supreme Court cases dealing with the relationship between government and religion.
9_27	0.092363324	The Supreme Court declared in Reynolds vs.
