9_29	0.095791166	Since then, justices like Potter Stewart and William Rehnquist have argued that Jefferson's words were misused.
9_30	0.092275928	The FBI discovered that Jefferson had crossed out the word ``eternal'' preceding ``separation of Church and State'' _ as some scholars had correctly guessed years before _ and inked over ``the duties of my station, which are merely temporal''.
9_31	0.088602048	That last word meant secular, as opposed to spiritual.
9_32	0.09025244	In his essay, Hutson surmised that Jefferson removed these phrases because they might sound ``too anti-religious to pious New England ears''.
