9_34	0.091047274	1, 1802, was meant to reassure the Baptists of Connecticut, who were suffering persecution from the Congregationalists in control of that state.
9_35	0.092127577	Jefferson also wrote that as president, he would not proclaim national feast days and thanksgivings.
9_36	0.092063875	But Hutson said that Jefferson omitted that section because his advisers warned that it might offend potential political allies.
